The paper discusses the development of a neural network model for knowledge graph completion, which involves tasks related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also deals with databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as it aims to fill in missing information and determine the veracity of declarative statements. Finally, the paper may also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with finding and validating information in a knowledge graph.
